# Spec-Driven Development (Source of Truth)

This repo is a SaaS base template (Clerk, Billing, Neon+Drizzle, OpenAI, shadcn/ui already set up).
We build the new product strictly from JSON specs.

## Source of Truth Files
All product flow and output is defined by JSON specs stored in `/specs`.

Rules:
- Do NOT invent new questions, states, artifacts, or views.
- Implement exactly what the specs say.
- If a spec seems incomplete, create the minimal TODO comment in code instead of guessing.

## Required Spec Architecture
- Questions render from `phaseX.questions.json`
- Phase logic runs from `phaseX.process.json` state machine
- AI outputs validate against `phaseX.artifacts.json` schemas
- UI views render from `phaseX.views.json`
- Final dashboard renders from `final_dashboard.views.json`
- Global UI rules come from `app.ui.json`
- DB model must match `app.data_model.json`
- PDF export must match `pdf_export.spec.json`

## Refactor Safety
- Keep existing infra intact (Clerk auth/billing, Neon+Drizzle, OpenAI, shadcn/ui, proxy/layout).
- Do not re-implement auth/billing/db connections if already present.
